<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[192,1440,194,538]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,316,194,218]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos-Silva &amp; Wappes, 2017" authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Wappes" authorityYear="2017" box="[333,568,194,218]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Coleoxestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hovorei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[333,568,194,218]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Coleoxestia hovorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[578,674,194,217]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[692,818,194,218]" captionStart="Figures 27–39. 27–29" captionStartId="19.[192,288,1801,1823]" captionTargetBox="[254,1377,195,1776]" captionTargetId="figure-86@19.[251,1380,192,1785]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figures 27–39. 27–29, Coleoxestia fragosoi sp. nov., holotype male: 27) Profemur. 28) Mesofemur. 29) Metafemur. 30–32, C. errata, holotype male: 30) Profemur. 31) Mesofemur. 32) Metafemur. 33–39, Coleoxestia hovorei sp. nov., holotype male: 33) Dorsal habitus. 34) Ventral habitus. 35) Lateral habitus. 36) Profemur. 37) Mesofemur. 38) Metafemur. 39) Head." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5169128" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5169128/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Fig. 33-39</figureCitation>
) differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gounelle" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[992,1138,194,218]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Coleoxestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femorata">
<emphasis box="[992,1138,194,218]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">C. femorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as follows: basal antennomeres sparsely pubescent; pronotum less distinctly plicate; elytra less distinctly coriaceous, mainly toward apex, without minute setae throughout. In 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gounelle" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[827,972,258,282]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Coleoxestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femorata">
<emphasis box="[827,972,258,282]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">C. femorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the basal antennomeres (
<figureCitation box="[1296,1382,257,282]" captionStart="Figures 4–16. 4–8" captionStartId="17.[192,288,1788,1810]" captionTargetBox="[268,1358,196,1767]" captionTargetId="figure-114@17.[261,1370,192,1776]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figures 4–16. 4–8, Coleoxestia clarkei sp. nov.: 4) Holotype female, dorsal habitus. 5) Holotype female, ventral habitus. 6) Holotype female, lateral habitus. 7) Paratype male, dorsal habitus. 8) Holotype female, head. 9–12, C. eyai sp. nov., holotype male: 9) Dorsal habitus. 10) Ventral habitus. 11) Lateral habitus. 12) Head. 13) C. chemsaki sp. nov., holotype male, metatarsus. 14) C. aurigena, holotype female, metatarsus. 15) C. femorata, male, antennomere III. 16) C. chemsaki sp. nov., holotype male, antennomere III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5169122" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5169122/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
) are distinctly pubescent, the pronotum is more distinctly plicate (
<figureCitation box="[936,1020,290,314]" captionStart="Figures 17–26. 17–21" captionStartId="18.[192,288,1846,1868]" captionTargetBox="[248,1390,200,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-84@18.[248,1393,192,1828]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figures 17–26. 17–21, Coleoxestia chemsaki sp. nov., holotype male: 17) Dorsal habitus. 18) Ventral habitus. 19) Lateral habitus. 20) Head. 21) C. femorata, male, dorsal habitus. 22–25, Coleoxestia fragosoi sp. nov., holotype male: 22) Dorsal habitus. 23) Ventral habitus. 24) Lateral habitus. 25) Head. 26) C. errata, holotype male, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5169126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5169126/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
) and the elytra are more distinctly coriaceous with minute setae throughout (
<figureCitation box="[706,792,322,346]" captionStart="Figures 17–26. 17–21" captionStartId="18.[192,288,1846,1868]" captionTargetBox="[248,1390,200,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-84@18.[248,1393,192,1828]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figures 17–26. 17–21, Coleoxestia chemsaki sp. nov., holotype male: 17) Dorsal habitus. 18) Ventral habitus. 19) Lateral habitus. 20) Head. 21) C. femorata, male, dorsal habitus. 22–25, Coleoxestia fragosoi sp. nov., holotype male: 22) Dorsal habitus. 23) Ventral habitus. 24) Lateral habitus. 25) Head. 26) C. errata, holotype male, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5169126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5169126/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
). It differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins and Monne" authorityYear="2005" box="[987,1096,322,345]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Coleoxestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="errata">
<emphasis box="[987,1096,322,345]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">C. errata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1110,1194,322,346]" captionStart="Figures 17–26. 17–21" captionStartId="18.[192,288,1846,1868]" captionTargetBox="[248,1390,200,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-84@18.[248,1393,192,1828]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figures 17–26. 17–21, Coleoxestia chemsaki sp. nov., holotype male: 17) Dorsal habitus. 18) Ventral habitus. 19) Lateral habitus. 20) Head. 21) C. femorata, male, dorsal habitus. 22–25, Coleoxestia fragosoi sp. nov., holotype male: 22) Dorsal habitus. 23) Ventral habitus. 24) Lateral habitus. 25) Head. 26) C. errata, holotype male, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5169126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5169126/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) mainly by the body more robust and the femora (
<figureCitation box="[542,671,354,378]" captionStart="Figures 27–39. 27–29" captionStartId="19.[192,288,1801,1823]" captionTargetBox="[254,1377,195,1776]" captionTargetId="figure-86@19.[251,1380,192,1785]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figures 27–39. 27–29, Coleoxestia fragosoi sp. nov., holotype male: 27) Profemur. 28) Mesofemur. 29) Metafemur. 30–32, C. errata, holotype male: 30) Profemur. 31) Mesofemur. 32) Metafemur. 33–39, Coleoxestia hovorei sp. nov., holotype male: 33) Dorsal habitus. 34) Ventral habitus. 35) Lateral habitus. 36) Profemur. 37) Mesofemur. 38) Metafemur. 39) Head." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5169128" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5169128/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Fig. 36–38</figureCitation>
) thicker than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins and Monne" authorityYear="2005" box="[871,980,354,377]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Coleoxestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="errata">
<emphasis box="[871,980,354,377]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">C. errata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
